'For now, arithmetic is not sensitive to whitespace:

:p 1.0+1.0
> 2.

:p 1.0 +1.0
> 2.

:p 1.0+ 1.0
> 2.

:p 1.0 + 1.0
> 2.

:p 1.0-1.0
> 0.

:p 1.0 -1.0
> 0.

:p 1.0- 1.0
> 0.

:p 1.0 - 1.0
> 0.

'Applying a function to a negative literal thus requires parentheses.

f = \x. x + 10.

:p f -1.0   -- parses as (-) f (-1.0)
> Type error:
> Expected: (Float32 -> Float32)
>   Actual: Float32
>
> :p f -1.0   -- parses as (-) f (-1.0)
>       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

:p f (-1.0)
> 9.

'Lambdas can have specific arrow annotations.

lam1 = \{n}. \x:(Fin n). ordinal x
:t lam1
> ((n:Nat) ?-> (Fin n) -> Nat)

lam4 = \{n m}. (Fin n, Fin m)
:t lam4
> (Nat ?-> Nat ?-> (Type & Type))

:p (
    1
    +
    2
   )
> 3

:p
  xs = [1,2,3]
  for i.
    if xs.i > 1
      then 0
      else 1
> [1, 0, 0]

:p
  run_state 5 \ref.
    n = get ref
    for_ i:(Fin n).
      ref := get ref + 1
> ((), 10)

